This has to be the best Music Video ever shot
It starts by Abdullah Hannan singing about his depression and anxietal thoughts, He sees Kaavish and the musicians setting up for their performance,  but he doesnt go there....
When the old women gives him the flower, he decides to stay and listen to Kaavish on the stairs
Kaavish (Senior Artist) gives hope to Abdullah Hannan (Upcoming Artist) in his verses...
By the end of it he understood Kaavish's message, as he hums the melody Kaavish had sung...
Brilliant!

snippet.textDisplay:
" Warsa" is the focal point of the song. As to what Time and Life has made you inherit.
So Warsa is a junction from where two paths emerge. Giving you choice to deal with what has possessed you. 

Abdul Hannan, the one with pain and hurt that life has inflicted upon him, pauses for a moment look at the brighter path, but then wanders into a darker lonely one with closed doors and windows.
In the same moment, Kavish, not alone, with his friends passes him and takes the very path that Hanan doesnt, which has colours, paintings, books, music and places with open doors and people.

Now Hanan is shown to passing legend Abida Parveen on the brick wall, translating his feelings 'Patharoon aaj meray sar par barsatay kyun ho.....'

But Hanan has not completely given up, there is some hope flickering and there are few fond memories, that seldom flashes in front of him like that lady and a flower.
This glimmer of hope ascends him to sit down for a while on that flight of stairs, with flower still in his hands. He waits and looks up seeking hope. 

Here Kavish takes over, who himself had been through pain and eventually found solace and truth inside him. 
He has now surrounded himself with 'Warsa' of arts, books, colours, music, paintings. Everything is open. People too.

Kavish completes, look left towards Hanan, complete darkness for a second, and then Hanan humming the tunes of hope with veins of light running in front of him.
He has heard the Voice.

This song is about the choices you make in Life. We all go through hurt and pain.
It depends which path you take.
Choice is yours and so is your Voice. Listen!
